  "summary": "Malicious code in driftpin (npm)",
  "details": "Driftpin@1.0.0, described as an SVG sanitizer, is a remote-code-execution dropper. Its index.js exports a getPlugin() function that makes an HTTPS GET request to jsonkeeper[.]com/b/3P9BF, parses the JSON response, and passes the 'model' field directly to eval() — enabling the remote endpoint to execute arbitrary JavaScript on the installer's machine.",
